<p>At the beginning of this year, I found myself hundreds of miles from home, in a strange neighborhood. It was the first night of a hitchhiking trip across the country, and I was looking for a place to roll out my sleeping bag.</p>

<p>The LA lights twinkled in the distance as dusk fell.</p>

